The Duke of Edinburgh was presented with the insignia of his Australian knighthood by the Queen at Windsor Castle on Wednesday . 
  He was recommended for the honour by Australian Prime Minister Tony Abbott on Australia Day in January . 
  The Queen presented the Duke with the award on Wednesday despite criticism of the decision . 
  The citation recognises his long service to the British monarchy and the Commonwealth . 
  The Duke served in the Royal Navy during the Second World War . 
 